LTG H. R. McMaster delivered a speech at the Reagan National Defense Forum, discussing the need for America to reclaim its strategic confidence. He emphasized the importance of understanding American values, utilizing all instruments of power, recognizing threats, and adapting to the dynamic security environment. He mentioned the upcoming unveiling of the Trump administration's National Security Strategy, which will focus on protecting the homeland, advancing prosperity, preserving peace through strength, and enhancing American influence. McMaster also highlighted President Trump's commitment to American values and principles through actions taken in response to global challenges. He concluded by expressing the administration's dedication to learning from the past to effectively address today's security challenges.